    <item>
      <title>Azure DevOps Git Repos Not Showing in Build Pipeline: Fixing Broken Repo Connections</title>
      <link>https://kasdevtech.com/devops/azuredevops-gitreposnotshowinginbuild-pipeline/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://kasdevtech.com/devops/azuredevops-gitreposnotshowinginbuild-pipeline/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Seeing this error when trying to trigger a pipeline from your Azure DevOps repo?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Error: The repository ‘&lt;repo-name&gt;’ could not be found or no longer exists.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;common-causes&#34;&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Repository renamed or deleted&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Permissions changed in the project&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;PAT token expired (for GitHub or external repos)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;fixing-the-issue&#34;&gt;Fixing the Issue&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;azure-repos-git&#34;&gt;Azure Repos Git&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Navigate to &lt;code&gt;Repos&lt;/code&gt; in your project&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Check if the repo still exists and hasn’t been renamed&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Confirm the branch in your trigger matches the YAML&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34; data-lang=&#34;yaml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;trigger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;branches&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#0550ae&#34;&gt;include&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;- main&lt;span style=&#34;color:#fff&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;github-repositories&#34;&gt;GitHub Repositories&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Go to Project Settings → Service Connections&#xA;Open your GitHub connection&#xA;Re-authenticate or update the PAT/token&#xA;Ensure scopes: repo, workflow, admin:repo_hook&lt;/p&gt;</description>
